From: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
Subject: [PATCH 01/12] nvidia-390xx: remove DRM_LEGACY dependency (kernel 5.18+)

Kernel 5.18 removed the DRM_LEGACY Kconfig symbol and all references
to legacy DRM. The nvidia-390xx driver uses drm_legacy_* functions that
no longer exist. This patch replaces them with stubs.

Signed-off-by: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
---
 kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-drv.c | 14 ++++++--------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-drv.c b/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-drv.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-drv.c
+++ b/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-drv.c
@@ -1,8 +1,6 @@
-#if defined(NV_DRM_DRIVER_HAS_LEGACY_DEV_LIST)
-    .firstopen    = nv_drm_firstopen,
-    .lastclose    = nv_drm_lastclose,
-    .preclose     = nv_drm_preclose,
-#endif
+    /* DRM_LEGACY removed in kernel 5.18 - Apollo patch */
